Indonesia Stocks: Astra Agro, International Nickel, Pyridam

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-08-09T09:24:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/indonesia-stocks-astra-agro-energi-mega-international-nickel.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  declined 115.15 points, or 3
percent, to 3,735.12, falling for a sixth day in the longest
losing streak since the six days ended Nov. 24, 2008.  Metal producers: PT International Nickel  Indonesia  (INCO
IJ), the nation’s largest producer of the metal, retreated 4.7
percent to 3,525 rupiah. PT Timah (TINS IJ), Indonesia’s biggest
tin mining company, fell 4.6 percent to 1,980 rupiah. Nickel
futures lost 5.6 percent to $21,250 a metric ton in  London 
yesterday and tin slumped 7.6 percent to $22,505 a ton.  Palm oil producers: PT Astra Agro Lestari (AALI IJ), the
nation’s biggest plantation stock by market value, dropped 4.9
percent to 21,200 rupiah. PT Bakrie Sumatera Plantations (UNSP
IJ) declined 5.2 percent to 365 rupiah.  Palm oil  for October
delivery dropped as much as 2.5 percent to 2,920 ringgit ($959)
a metric ton in  Kuala Lumpur . The contract fell to the lowest
level in more than nine months yesterday.  PT Pyridam Farma (PYFA IJ), a pharmaceutical company, fell
5.6 percent to 170 rupiah, the lowest close since May 4, after
reporting second-quarter net income plunged 71 percent from the
previous quarter to 1.34 billion rupiah ($156,00).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  